		  communities determines to a large part the response to soil
		  legacies. Furthermore, the responses to soil legacies of
		  herbivores feeding on the plant communities that we
		  observed, suggests that in natural ecosystems, the
		  vegetation history may also have an influence on
		  contemporary herbivore assemblages. This opens up exciting
		  new areas in plant–insect research and can have important
		  implications for insect pest management.},
