  abstract	= {Grasses have been considered to primarily employ tolerance
		  in lieu of defense in mitigating damage caused by
		  herbivory. Yet a number of mechanisms have been identified
		  in grasses, which may deter feeding by grazers. These
		  include enhanced silicon uptake, hosting of toxin-producing
